Wrap in tensor_apply_function.","notes":"Fixed in this commit. Wrapped tensor_repeat_interleave in tensor_apply_function with sum-of-R backward: grad_input[i] = sum_{j: j / R == i} grad_output[j]. Each input element gets the sum of the R consecutive output gradients that came from it. Preserved the byte-size overflow check (output count alone can fit in usize even when out_len * 8 bytes overflows). Added repeat_interleave_propagates_gradient_via_sum_of_repeats regression test (x=[3,5], R=4 → grad=[4,4]). ft-api lib tests: 1165.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-30T22:11:55.471995742Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-30T22:14:14.396719222Z","closed_at":"2026-04-30T22:14:14.393277046Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
